review_blob: Obviously not everyones taste. Not to be confused with BEER. On an even playing field with the likes of alchoholic ginger beer. Being a fan of root beer, this is a welcome addition to the market without paying the extortionate prices for non alchoholic root beer imported from America. The only thing missing (from memories of the old soda fountains and A&W; drive in restaurants) is the frosty mug and a generous dollop of vanilla ice cream floated on top. Root Beer Float anyone?
